<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FF86FFDC6DC2FBFDFD2BAF96" pageId="34" pageNumber="1547" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFF86FFDC6DC2FBFDFD2BAF96" blockId="34.[178,1085,1120,1172]" pageId="34" pageNumber="1547">
Diagnosis: Within 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FF86FFDC6CCBFBFDFDCFAF74" box="[443,602,1120,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="1547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Platynopterinae">Platynopterinae</taxonomicName>
only members of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FF86FFDC6E64FBFDFC37AF77" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1876" box="[788,930,1120,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarandocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="1555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FF86FFDC6E64FBFDFC37AF77" box="[788,930,1120,1141]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="1547">Tarandocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a collateral branch on antennomeres 9 and 10 (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF86FFDC6F46FBE3FD27AF96" box="[566,690,1150,1172]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="1547">Figs. 46, 47</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FF86FFDD6DC2FB3EFE23AF27" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="1548" pageId="34" pageNumber="1547" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFF86FFDD6DC2FB3EFE23AF27" blockId="34.[178,1086,1187,1590]" lastBlockId="35.[178,1086,219,1061]" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="1548" pageId="34" pageNumber="1547">
Description: Size: Length 9.0-19.0 mm; width 4.5-8.0. Form: Elytra trapezoidal, posterior half of elytra may be flared, elytral posterior angle broadly rounded. Integumental color: Antenna always black; mandible black, other mouthparts flavotestaceous to light brown; cranium mostly black, epicranium narrowly flavotestaceous, cranium rarely with narrowly flavotestaceous frons; pronotum unicolorous or bicolorous, rarely tricolorous, when unicolorous flavotestaceous, when bicolorous upper sides flavotestaceous and at lower sides and disc black, black disc region may show narrow or broad flavotestaceous line, lower sides rarely red, pronotal venter flavotestaceous or brown; elytra mostly black or mostly flavotestaceous, black regions may have bluish tinge; legs entirely black or black in distal third and decreasingly flavotestaceous from profemur to metafemur; pterothorax and abdomen black. Vestiture: Integument highly setose, funicular antennomeres densely setose, cranium and pronotum densely vested with decumbent setae, elytra densely vested with short 2° setae and fewer 1° setae that become more prominent along epipleural and sutural margins; legs highly setose. Head (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6DC9FF46FEA2ABF3" box="[185,311,219,241]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Figs. 48-50</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6C39FF46FEE6ABF3" box="[329,371,219,241]" captionStart="Figs 103-108" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1194,1216]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,219,1178]" captionTargetId="figure-219@33.[178,1085,219,1178]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 103-108: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides (103-107) and Plocamocera coactilis (108). (103) Head, frontal view; (104) Antennal capitulum; (105) Pronotal disc; (106) Antennal funicle; (107) Pronotal disc showing insipient trichobothrium; (108) Pronotal trichobothrium (8 bothrium, 9 trabiculae, 10 trich)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282513/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">103</figureCitation>
): Cranial setose punctation small; frons roughly sculptured; eyes bulging, finely faceted and deeply broadly incised along frontal margin; antenna (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD697AFF65FF6DAA28" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Figs. 46, 47</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6C75FE88FEF6AA29" box="[261,355,277,299]" captionStart="Figs 103-108" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1194,1216]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,219,1178]" captionTargetId="figure-219@33.[178,1085,219,1178]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 103-108: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides (103-107) and Plocamocera coactilis (108). (103) Head, frontal view; (104) Antennal capitulum; (105) Pronotal disc; (106) Antennal funicle; (107) Pronotal disc showing insipient trichobothrium; (108) Pronotal trichobothrium (8 bothrium, 9 trabiculae, 10 trich)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282513/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">104, 106</figureCitation>
) capitate, inserted at level of eye incision (= ocular notch); antennal carina very prominent, comprised of 11 antennomeres, scape very robust, pedicel subquadrate, funicular antennomeres transverse, capitulum very long, about a third times longer that length of other antennomeres combined, antennomeres 9 and 10 with collateral branches, branches more prominent in males (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6FB8FE17FC82AAA2" box="[712,791,394,416]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
) than in females (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6E90FE17FBA4AAA3" box="[992,1073,394,417]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
); labrum (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6C78FE35FEC6AABC" box="[264,339,424,446]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
) not deeply incised, transverse tormal process horizontal and contiguous; mandible (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6C51FE58FEFBAAD9" box="[289,366,453,475]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
) robust, dens well developed, penicillus reduced; maxilla (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6EADFE58FBA3AAD9" box="[989,1078,453,475]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 57a</figureCitation>
) well developed, terminal palpomere subsecuriform, laterolacinia present; labium (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6964FE7FFF58A917" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
) well developed, terminal palpomere subsecuriform; gula (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6E5AFE62FCE3A914" box="[810,886,511,534]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
) triangular. Thorax (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6DC9FD80FEA3A931" box="[185,310,541,563]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Figs. 51, 52</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6C31FD80FEFEA931" box="[321,363,541,563]" captionStart="Figs 103-108" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1194,1216]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,219,1178]" captionTargetId="figure-219@33.[178,1085,219,1178]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 103-108: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides (103-107) and Plocamocera coactilis (108). (103) Head, frontal view; (104) Antennal capitulum; (105) Pronotal disc; (106) Antennal funicle; (107) Pronotal disc showing insipient trichobothrium; (108) Pronotal trichobothrium (8 bothrium, 9 trabiculae, 10 trich)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282513/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">105</figureCitation>
): Pronotum with incipient trichobothrium (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6E53FD80FCE9A931" box="[803,892,541,563]" captionStart="Figs 103-108" captionStartId="33.[178,218,1194,1216]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,219,1178]" captionTargetId="figure-219@33.[178,1085,219,1178]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 103-108: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides (103-107) and Plocamocera coactilis (108). (103) Head, frontal view; (104) Antennal capitulum; (105) Pronotal disc; (106) Antennal funicle; (107) Pronotal disc showing insipient trichobothrium; (108) Pronotal trichobothrium (8 bothrium, 9 trabiculae, 10 trich)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282513/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 107</figureCitation>
), quadrate or elongate, side margins rounded at middle, anterior margin linear, prebasal depression feebly developed, dorsolateral carina not extended to anterior margin of pronotum, carina joins pronotal hem at pronotal posterior angle; elytra trapezoidal, sometimes increasingly widened to rounded posterior angles, with discal carinae; mesoscutellum quadrate; protibial anterior margin spinous; ungues without denticle (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6F91FD32FCAEA9C7" box="[737,827,687,709]" captionStart="Figs 93-96" captionStartId="31.[178,218,963,985]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,219,944]" captionTargetId="figure-335@31.[178,1085,219,944]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 93-96b: Morphological organs of Aspitonis alarutinis (93-95), Pilosirus brunnoi (96a), Tarandocerus lycoides (96b). (93) Antennal funicle; (94) Insipient trichobothrium on the pronotal disc; 95) Pronotal disc; (96a) Pronotal disc; (96b) Metatarsal ungues." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294872" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294872/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 96b</figureCitation>
); tibial spur formula 0-1- 1; tarsal pulvillar formula 3-3-3; metathoracic wing as in 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6E71FD51FCCDA9E0" box="[769,856,716,738]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 61a</figureCitation>
; metendosternite (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6964FD51FF59A802" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
) with furcal lamina. Abdomen: Six visible sternites; pygidium rounded distally in both sexes, rarely incised in male. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6FA1FC9AFCEAA81F" box="[721,895,775,797]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Figs. 58, 59, 60</figureCitation>
): Aedeagus short, tegmen well or feebly sclerotized, lobate distally, fimbriate, phallus well sclerotized; spicular fork (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6C33FCDFFE0EA855" box="[323,411,833,856]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 57b</figureCitation>
) comprised of two narrow plates that connect at proximal fourth, intraspicular plate narrow and long. Female genitalia: Ovipositor short; dorsal and ventral laminae trilobed. Alimentary canal (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6F3DFCE1FD3DA890" box="[589,680,892,914]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 61b</figureCitation>
): Proventriculus moderately developed; ventriculus narrow, papillae poorly developed; 4 cryptonephridial Malpighian tubules. Male mesodermal reproductive organs (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6F3FFC2AFD3DA8CF" box="[591,680,951,973]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 61c</figureCitation>
): Two pairs of accessory glands; testis comprised of more than 40 follicles. Female mesodermal reproductive organs (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFF87FFDD6EA7FC49FBA7A8E8" box="[983,1074,980,1002]" captionStart="Figs 46-61" captionStartId="15.[178,218,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[198,1090,257,1295]" captionTargetId="figure-1@15.[178,1108,228,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 46-61a: Morphological organs of Tarandocerus lycoides. (46) Antenna, male; (47) Antenna, female; (48) Head, frontal view; (49) Head, ventral view; (50) Head, dorsal view; (51) Pronotum, ventral view; (52) Pronotum, dorsal view; (53) Metendosternite; (54) Labrum; (55) Mandible; (56) Labium; (57a) Maxilla; (57b) Spicular fork; (58) Tegmen, ventral view; (59) Tegmen, lateral view; (60) Phallus; (61a) Metathoracic wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282511/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Fig. 61d</figureCitation>
): Spermathecal capsule well sclerotized; spermathecal gland attached to base of capsule; bursa copulatrix saccular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FF87FFDD6DC2FBA9FB97AF48" box="[178,1026,1076,1098]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFF87FFDD6DC2FBA9FB97AF48" blockId="35.[178,1026,1076,1098]" box="[178,1026,1076,1098]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">
Distribution: The members of this genus range from 
<collectingCountry id="2CD24C9BFF87FFDD6E58FBA9FCE0AF48" box="[808,885,1076,1098]" name="Mexico" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">México</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="2CD24C9BFF87FFDD6EE5FBA9FC6BAF48" box="[917,1022,1076,1098]" name="Argentina" pageId="35" pageNumber="1548">Argentina</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
